docs.summary: Wix forms allows site owners to easily create custom forms on their websites and get submissions from their visitors

This webhook is triggered whenever a site visitor fills out a Wix form on your user's site 
 (Note that there are several other form apps/options available for user sites, but they will not trigger this webhook)

permissions.name: Read Form Submissions
permissions.description: Request permission to read the site's Wix Forms submissions.

members.name: collectionId
members.doc: ID of form submissions collection in WixData

members.name: submissions
members.doc: Number of times the form was submitted on the website

members.name: plugins
members.doc: List of plugins associated with this form

members.name: collectionId
members.doc: ID of form submissions collection in WixData

members.name: pluginsV2
members.doc: List of plugins associated with this form

members.name: inboxOptOut
members.doc:
*
 Forms with submissions that:
 1. Email notification is rendered without Respond Now button

members.name: externalId
members.doc: Form external ID in a given site.

members.name: revision
members.doc: Revision number. When updating, include the existing `revision` to prevent conflicting updates.

members.name: publishedStatus
members.doc:
Form publication status.

 - `DRAFT` — Created in the editor, not published yet.
 - `DISCARDED` — Deleted before publishing.
 - `PUBLISHED` — Published to the live site.
 - `DELETED` — Removed from the site after publishing.

members.name: metadata
members.doc: Additional metadata related to the form.

members.name: source
members.doc: Source of the form - what created it

members.name: externalId
members.doc: Field external ID in a given form.

members.name: mode
members.doc:
Controls when the visitor will be subscribed to site emails.

 `ON_SUBMIT` — Subscribe when the visitor submits the form.
 `AFTER_CONFIRMATION` — Subscribe when the visitor's email is verified.

members.name: dateLimit
members.doc: Sets an end date for form submissions.

members.name: operator
members.doc: Operation on the date. Currently supports `BEFORE` only.

members.name: type
members.doc:
Form attribute.

 - `SUBSCRIPTION` —
    [Email subscription form](https://support.wix.com/en/article/adding-and-setting-up-a-get-subscribers-form).
    Used in combination with `subscriptionForm`.
 - `REGISTRATION` — Site member registration form.
 - `PAYMENT` — Payment form. If used, the site owner must have or set up a
    [payment provider](https://support.wix.com/en/article/available-payment-providers-6803928).
 - `CAPTCHA` — Form with a
    [reCAPTCHA field](https://support.wix.com/en/article/protecting-your-form-from-spam-with-a-captcha-field).
 - `MULTI_STEP` — [Multi-step form](https://support.wix.com/en/article/adding-and-setting-up-a-multi-step-form)
 - `NO_INBOX_NOTIFICATION` — Inbox notifications on form submissions won't trigger.
 - `LIMIT_RULES` — Form with submission limits,
    such as an end date or submissions per time period.
    Used in combination with `formWithLimitRules`.

members.name: subscriptionSettings
members.doc:
Subscription form details.
 Used if `FormAttribute.type` is set to `SUBSCRIPTION`.

members.name: limitSettings
members.doc:
Submission limit settings.
 Used if `FormAttribute.type` is set to `LIMIT_RULES`.

members.name: externalId
members.doc: Field external ID in a given form.

members.name: externalId
members.doc: Form external ID in a given site

members.name: fields
members.doc:
List of form fields. On update, if populated, all existing fields will be replaced
 by the given array.

members.name: formAttributes
members.doc:
Form type and submission limits. On update, if populated, all existing attributes
 will be replaced by the given array.

members.name: paths
members.doc: The set of field mask paths.

members.name: limit
members.doc: The number of items to load

members.name: offset
members.doc: number of items to skip in the current sort order

members.name: count
members.doc: The number of items returned in this response

members.name: total
members.doc: The total number of items that match the query

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: A flag that indicates the server failed to calculate 'total' field

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by

members.name: fields
members.doc: Projection on the result object - list of specific field names to return. If fieldsets are also specified, return the union of fieldsets and fields

members.name: fieldsets
members.doc: Projection on the result object - list of named projections. E.g. "basic" will return id and name fields. Specifying multiple fieldsets will return the union of fields from all. Specifying fieldsets and fields will also return the union of fields.

members.name: revision
members.doc:
Revision number. When updating, include the existing `revision`
 to prevent conflicting updates.

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc:
Set of fields to update.
 Fields that aren't included in `fieldMask.paths` are ignored.
 See
 [Field Masks in Update Requests](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/field-masks-in-update-requests)
 for details on working with field masks.

* Form status lifecycle: Create form in editor +-------+ | Draft | +---+---+ Publish site | Publish site with the form +---------+---------+ without the | | form v v +-----+-----+ +-----+-----+ | Published | | Discarded | +-----+-----+ +-----------+ | v Republish site +----+----+ without the | Deleted | form +---------+ Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • PUBLISHED - Form is published and available on the site
  • DELETED - Form was published but removed from the site
  • DRAFT - Form was created in the editor, but was not yet published
  • DISCARDED - Form was created in the editor, but deleted before the site was published
  • ARCHIVED - Form marked as archived

Possible values are:
  • FORM_BUILDER - Regular form
  • GET_SUBSCRIBERS - Get subscribers form plugin
  • REGISTRATION_FORM - Registration form plugin
  • PAYMENT_FORM - Payment form plugin
  • CAPTCHA - Form secured with CAPTCHA
  • MULTI_STEP - Multi step form
  • INBOX_OPT_OUT - See PluginV2
  • LIMIT_RULES - Submissions limiter plugin

Possible values are:
  • TOTAL
  • MINUTE
  • HOUR
  • DAY
  • WEEK
  • MONTH
  • YEAR

Possible values are:

`NullValue` is a singleton enumeration to represent the null value for the `Value` type union. The JSON representation for `NullValue` is JSON `null`. Possible values are:
  • NULL_VALUE - Null value.

Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • PUBLISHED - Form is published and available on the site.
  • DELETED - Form was published but removed from the site.
  • DRAFT - Form was created in the editor, but was not yet published.
  • DISCARDED - Form was created in the editor, but deleted before the site was published.
  • ARCHIVED - Form marked as archived

Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • ON_SUBMIT - User is added to the subscription list directly after filling out the form
  • AFTER_CONFIRMATION - User is added to the subscription list after they verify their mail address
